description:
senior ai engineer

location: los angeles (on\-site / hybrid, negotiable)

reports to: technical lead / cto

about sightglobal

sightglobal is a professional firm specializing in investigation and consulting services, dedicated to providing clients with high\-quality investigative analysis, risk assessment, and strategic consulting solutions. we are currently in a critical strategic transformation period — deeply integrating cutting\-edge artificial intelligence technologies into our traditional investigation and consulting business. we are developing ai\-powered intelligent investigation tools, smart data analysis systems, and automated decision\-support platforms to help clients address complex challenges more efficiently and accurately.

while we still center our core on consulting services, we have a clear commitment to expanding into the artificial intelligence field. we welcome technical talent with big\-tech backgrounds to join us in building the next generation of intelligent consulting and investigation solutions. here, you will directly participate in technology implementation from 0 to 1, rather than remaining at the theoretical level.

we are looking for

we invite outstanding talent with substantial project experience at top technology companies to join us — especially senior engineers from apple, openai, google, meta, microsoft, and similar leading firms. you will help sightglobal deeply integrate artificial intelligence technologies with our investigation and consulting business, driving the company’s rapid development toward ai\-powered intelligent consulting.

key responsibilities

design, develop, and optimize large language models (llms), multimodal models, and ai agent systems for applications in intelligent investigation, data analysis, and risk prediction scenarios;

build end\-to\-end ai solutions, including data processing, model fine\-tuning, rag architecture, agent framework integration, and production environment deployment;

collaborate closely with the investigation and consulting teams to integrate ai capabilities into existing consulting products and services, improving investigation efficiency and analytical accuracy;

track and experiment with the latest ai research advancements to solve real business challenges in data processing, pattern recognition, and intelligent decision\-making;

participate in code reviews and system architecture design to ensure ai systems deliver high security, reliability, and scalability in consulting scenarios.

requirements

bachelor’s degree or higher in computer science, artificial intelligence, machine learning, or related fields;

3\+ years of hands\-on experience in ai/ml projects, with priority given to candidates with work experience at apple, openai, google, meta, or other top\-tier technology companies;

proficient in python and experienced with mainstream frameworks such as pytorch, tensorflow, and hugging face;

experience with large language model fine\-tuning, rag systems, langchain/llamaindex or other agent development, and large\-scale model deployment is strongly preferred;

solid understanding of data security, privacy protection, and enterprise\-level applications, with a strong interest in applying ai technologies to consulting and investigation scenarios;

excellent systems thinking, problem\-solving abilities, and strong teamwork \& communication skills; fluent in english.

what we offer

competitive salary and equity incentives (specific compensation negotiable based on experience);

access to top\-tier computational resources and greater technical ownership during this transformative period;

flexible work arrangements and a unique experience combining consulting business with cutting\-edge ai development;

continuous learning and growth opportunities (participation in industry conferences, internal tech talks, ai project experimentation, etc.);

comprehensive health benefits and team\-building activities.

why join sightglobal?

in large technology companies, you may focus on a single technical module. here, your technical expertise will directly drive our strategic transformation from traditional investigation and consulting to ai\-powered intelligent consulting. every contribution you make can quickly translate into real business value, helping us secure a leading position in the rapidly evolving ai era.

if you are passionate about applying artificial intelligence to real\-world business scenarios and want to play a core role in a company with a clear vision for transformation, we warmly welcome you to join us.

how to apply

please send your resume to hr@sightglobal.com (or the designated recruitment email on our website). in the email subject line, please indicate: “senior ai engineer \- \[your name]”.

we will review applications promptly and look forward to discussing your technical ideas and our transformation vision with you!

pay: $3,500\.00 \- $5,500\.00 per month

work location: hybrid remote in san diego, ca 92123
